{
  "texts": [
    "Munadi et al. (2020) combined deep learning techniques with image enhancement methodologies to tackle tuberculosis (TB) image classification.",
    "Their innovative approach involved utilizing Unsharp Masking (UM) and High-Frequency Emphasis Filtering (HEF) in conjunction with EfficientNet-B4, ResNet-50, and ResNet-18 models.",
    "By evaluating the performance of three image enhancement algorithms, their work demonstrated remarkable accuracy and Area Under Curve (AUC) scores, revealing the potential of their method for accurate TB image diagnosis.",
    "Lu et al. (2021) introduced a novel application of deep learning, particularly the use of a fully connected neural network (FCNN), to address impulse noise in degraded images with varying noise densities.",
    "What's noteworthy about their approach is the development of an FCNN mean filter that outperformed traditional mean/median filters, especially when handling low-noise density environments."
  ]
}